<subSubSection id="C3037492FFA8FF80E084282927FBBAB3" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA62719FFA8FF80E084282927FBBAB3" blockId="21.[151,1437,224,503]" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E08428292757BA22" bold="true" box="[199,317,333,359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">Remarks:</emphasis>
As discussed below, the specimens erroneously reported as 
<taxonomicName id="4C195C9AFFA8FF80E39C2828228ABA23" baseAuthorityName="Delle Chiaje" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[991,1248,332,358]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="squamata">
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E39C2828228ABA23" box="[991,1248,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">Amphipholis squamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF885AE8FFA8FF80E54A282827AFBACE" author="Attaran-Fariman, G. &amp; Beygmoradi, A." pageId="21" pageNumber="98" pagination="1254 - 1261" refId="ref13213" refString="Attaran-Fariman, G. &amp; Beygmoradi, A. (2016) Short communication: The first report of Amphipholis squamata (Delle Chiaje, 1829) (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Chabahar Bay - northern Oman Sea. Iranian Journal of Fisheries Sciences, 15, 1254 - 1261." type="journal article" year="2016">Attaran-Fariman &amp; Beygmoradi (2016)</bibRefCitation>
belong in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C195C9AFFA8FF80E2EB28142549BACF" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[680,803,368,394]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E2EB28142549BACF" box="[680,803,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">Amphiodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead. The specimen figured by them has a fully scaled disc, as is found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C195C9AFFA8FF80E13728F12462BAEB" authorityName="- A. M. Clark" authorityYear="1970" box="[372,520,404,431]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="microplax">
A. 
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E1DB28F02462BAEB" box="[408,520,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">microplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a sharp edge that possibly bears spiny processes that are typical for 
<taxonomicName id="4C195C9AFFA8FF80E51428F12686BA97" authorityName="- A. M. Clark" authorityYear="1970" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="microplax">
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E51428F12302BAEA" box="[1367,1384,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E53428F12686BA97" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">microplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C195C9AFFA8FF80E16128DD2406BA96" authority="(Stohr et al. 2010)" authorityName="Stohr" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Stohr" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[290,620,440,467]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="obtecta">
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E16128DD2759BA96" box="[290,307,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E10228DC27F9BA97" box="[321,403,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">obtecta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF885AE8FFA8FF80E1E128DC240EBA96" author="Stohr, S. &amp; Cinar, M. E. &amp; Dagli, E." box="[418,612,440,467]" pageId="21" pageNumber="98" pagination="45 - 57" refId="ref18476" refString="Stohr, S., Cinar, M. E. &amp; Dagli, E. (2010) Brittle stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from the southern coast of Turkey (eastern Mediterranean): new records and revision of Amphiodia obtecta Mortensen, 1940. Zootaxa, 2483 (1), 45 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2483.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">
Stöhr 
<emphasis id="B96DFB0BFFA8FF80E1AB28DD244ABA97" box="[488,544,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, the figures are not detailed enough to allow assignment of the specimen to a species.
</paragraph>
